State files an Amended Information charging Negligent operation of motor vehicle, contrary to Section 941.01(1) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  Motion granted.  No contest plea to the amended charge.  Convicted.  Sentence withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for one (1) year.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) Maintain full-time employment;
3) Successfully complete a driver safety course;
4) Pay $100.00 restitution to Norbert Braun, 6501 CTH J, Cato, WI 54230;
5) Apology to the victim's family, if agent believes more needs to be done;
6) Spend fifty-seven (57) days in jail, under the Huber Law, to commence on 10-21-14 by 6:00 p.m.
7) Pay costs of action; 
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights. 
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.  
Minutes.
